node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, the Apple Watch Series 7 is facing production issues and will be available in limited quantities at launch. Apple still plans to launch the new Apple Watch at the upcoming September event, however, Apple could launch it with limited availability or delay the launch to a later date.

#Apple #AppleWatch #iPhone13 #iPhone13Pro #Tech #AppleHub

node.text:
According to Bloomberg’s Mark Gurman, the upcoming Apple Watch Series 7 will come in 41mm and 45mm sizes, with the 45mm size featuring a larger 1.9” display (up from 1.78”) and a resolution of 396 x 484 (up from 368 x 448). The new watch will have multiple new watch faces that take advantage of the larger displays including a new Modular Max watch face that displays the digital time alongside a complication and can display longer complications stacked on top of each other below.

#Apple #AppleWatch #Series7 #Tech #AppleHub

Nikkei Asia is reporting that the upcoming Apple Watch Series 7 has been delayed due to its "complicated design" and production has been "temporarily halted.” The new watch will have blood pressure measurement capabilities that have complicated the production. Apple will likely announce the new Apple Watch at the upcoming September event, however, they may launch it at a later date. Render from @rendersbyian
